- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions building autonomous systems that comply with the doctrine of double effect. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses a first-order modal logic to formalize the doctrine. 
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses verifying that an AI system is compliant with the doctrine, which could involve security considerations. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the application of the doctrine to new technologies such as STRIPS-style planning and POMDP models.
